Problem:
class Simulation {
  int weatherCondition;  // 1 for sunny, 2 for rainy
  bool outdoorEvent;
  bool useUmbrellas;

  void checkWeather() {
    if (weatherCondition == 2) {
      outdoorEvent = false;
      useUmbrellas = true;
    } else {
      outdoorEvent = true;
      useUmbrellas = false;
    }
  }

  void forceOutdoorEvent() {
    outdoorEvent = true;
    if (weatherCondition == 2) {
      useUmbrellas = true;
    }
  }

  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Simulation sim = new Simulation();
    sim.weatherCondition = 2; // It's rainy
    sim.checkWeather();
    System.out.println("Outdoor Event: " + sim.outdoorEvent);
    System.out.println("Use Umbrellas: " + sim.useUmbrellas);
  }
}",

If the simulation is manually set to hold an outdoor event even on a rainy day, will umbrellas be used?
